records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
The defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing. The Court finds that the defendant's waiver is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made and binds the defendant over to Circuit Court Branch 1 for further proceedings.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, battery or threat to law enforcement officer as repeater.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 2, felony bail jumping as repeater.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 3 and 4.  Motion granted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to 
DOC for a total of five (5) years.
Conditions of probation:
1)	Pay court costs;
2)	pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3)	provide DNA sample;
4)	assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5)	have no contact with A.R.;
6)	any counseling, treatment, assessments as recommended by the agent;
7)	On count 1, spend one hundred twenty (120) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agent's discretion and upon order of the court.
Minutes.
